-- Russia's RTS Stock Index Climbs for Third Day This Week on Oil, U.S. Data
-- Alex Nicholson
-- 2010-07-08T06:18:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/russia-s-rts-stock-index-climbs-for-third-day-this-week-on-oil-u-s-data.html

          
          
             The dollar-denominated RTS Index
climbed for the third day this week, as crude oil advanced to a
one-week high after gains in U.S. retail sales spurred
speculation the global recovery is on track.  
 OAO Sberbank, the countryâ€™s biggest lender, and oil
producers OAO Lukoil and OAO Surgutneftegaz advanced. Those
movements pushed the RTS Index 1.5 percent higher to 1,372.33 as
of 10:15 a.m. in Moscow.  
 Crude for August delivery rose as much as $1.03, or 1.4
percent, to $75.10 a barrel in electronic trading on the New
York Mercantile Exchange.  
          
          


  


        